Kim Jong Il Gives On-site Guidance to Newly Built Pig Farm 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, gave on-the-spot guidance to pig farm No. 110 newly built by KPA servicepersons.
 After being briefed on the farm before a huge painting showing its panoramic view, he looked round the exterior and interior of the farm to learn in detail how it was built and is being operated. He highly appreciated the merits performed by the soldier-builders, greatly satisfied with the successful construction of the farm.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went round pig sties, assorted feed and processing factories and various other places of the farm to acquaint himself in detail with its technical equipment and breeding.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth important tasks which would serve as guidelines in managing and operating the farm and increasing the pork production, pleased to learn that the employees of the farm are mass-producing pork and quality processed products by establishing a scientific production system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to increase the production of pork on the farm, it is necessary to put the breeding on a scientific basis and make sustained efforts to raise the level of technical skill of the producers and, at the same time, to energetically push forward the work to introduce advanced technology, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that a scientific breeding system has been established at the chicken and pig farms that have mushroomed in recent years is now paying off profusely, he added that this reality eloquently proves that it is possible to bring about a change in the stock-breeding, too, in a brief span of time if full play is given to the people's revolutionary spirit and creative ingenuity on the basis of the advantages of the Korean-style socialist system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A solid material and technical foundation has been laid in the country to make a leap forward in the production of pork including the establishment of the system for breeding superior pedigree stock, he noted, underscoring the need to raise pigs in a big way by taking advantage of these favorable conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called on all fields and units to wage a dynamic popular movement to further develop the stock-breeding so as to provide the people with a more affluent and highly civilized life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong.

Kim Jong Il Meets Cambodian Great King 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, Monday visited the Jangsuwon State Guest House to meet the Great King Norodom Sihanouk of Cambodia on a visit to the DPRK.
 Present there were the Great Queen Norodom Monineath, the entourage of the great king and Cambodian ambassador to the DPRK Chhorn Hay. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The great king presented Kim Jong Il with a gift and expressed deep thanks to him for the splendid reconstruction of the state guest house and the cordial hospitality accorded to him during his stay in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il had a warm and friendly conversation with the great king.

Protest against Expansion of U.S. Military Base in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- At least 1,000 members of civic organizations and students in south Korea entered a fierce protest at a planned site for expansion of the U.S. military base in area of Taechu-ri, Phaengsong town, Phyongthaek City, Kyonggi Province, on May 5, according to the south Korean KBS. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The protesters broke through wire entanglements into the planned site two times and strongly denounced the Defence Ministry for designating the site as a "protection district of military facilities".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Huge military forces frantically cracked down on the protesters with deadly weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Therefore, there was a fierce clash between the protesters and military forces.

Japanese Reactionaries' Attempt to Grab Korea's Territory Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- Some time ago, the Japanese government informed the International Hydrographic Organization of its will to make measurements of waterway near Tok Islet until the end of June. In this regard, the Japanese ambassador in Seoul alleged that the waters to be measured is the exclusive economical waters of Japan. Even the Japanese chief executive said that Japan may resolutely take a physical countermeasure regarding the issue of Tok Islet.
 The Japanese reactionaries has tried in every way to grab Tok Islet, but never in such a brigandish way as now, says Rodong Sinmun Monday in a signed commentary.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's more naked moves for territorial expansion are a very grave and dangerous attempt. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To make the islet an area of international dispute and grab it is one of the cunning and impudent territorial rapacity methods peculiar to Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tok Islet is not a controversial territory whose owner is uncertain. It is well known to the world that the islet is a hereditary islet of Korea. Nevertheless, Japan is going to make the islet an international controversial area to grab it, which is an imprudent action that can be done only by robbers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are also attempting to invade the islet by force of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Insisting on dominium over the islet, Japan is resorting to ill-boding military moves. Japan is keen to commit "Self-Defense Forces" to sea near Tok Islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Marine resources are rich and natural gas and other energy resources are deposited plenty around the islet. The islet is very important militarily and strategically as it is situated near the Korean Peninsula. This is why the Japanese reactionaries are going to grab Tok Islet at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is foolish and reckless for them to grab the islet, an inalienable part of the Korean territory.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Throwing Overboard Pro-U.S. Conservative Forces 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- It is a realistic task for saving the south Korean people from misfortunes and pain and accelerating the independent reunification to achieve a great alliance against the conservative forces in south Korea.
 Rodong Sinmun Monday says this in a signed article. It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. conservatives in south Korea are treacherous forces as they have pursued anachronistic country-selling politics, bringing only misfortunes and pain to the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All sorts of misfortunes and pain of the south Korean people are chiefly attributable to the U.S. imperialists' policy of domination and subjugation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This being a hard reality, the Grand National Party in south Korea hell-bent on flunkeyism and dependence upon foreign forces has followed such country-selling politics as zealously backing and protecting the U.S. imperialists' presence in south Korea and domination over it and clinging to their coattails though the Korean nation lives in the June 15 era of  reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people have been subject to unspeakable sacrifices and sufferings under the tyrannical rule of the successive fascist dictatorial regimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the GNP and other pro-U.S. conservative forces are making desperate efforts to repeat the crime-woven past history. They are openly whitewashing the fascist repressive regimes of the past dictatorial forces, talking about what they call "the nature of their system" and "legacy of the right-wing," far from reflecting on the crimes committed by their predecessors. The GNP claims it will do something for the people whenever an opportunity presents itself, but it, in fact, turns its faces away from their misfortunes in pursuance of its partisan interests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are only stoking the inter-Korean confrontation, opposed to national reconciliation and reunification, and thus adding to the people's misfortunes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are dead-set against the independent reunification of Korea. They have not yet uttered even a word of support to the June 15 joint declaration but persistently pursued north-south confrontation under the patronage of their American master. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The formation of a great alliance against the conservative forces would pave the way for eliminating the root cause of misfortunes and pain of the south Korean people and carving out an independent life, the article concludes.

Rakrang Physical Rehabilitation Center Starts Operation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 8 (KCNA) -- The Rakrang Physical Rehabilitation Center located in Thongil Street, Pyongyang, has begun its operation on the occasion of the Day of the World Red Cross and the Red Crescent (May 8).
 The center, with a total floor space of 2,900 square meters, has been built on the site of 4,300 square meters by the joint efforts of the Central Committee of the DPRK Red Cross Society and the International Committee of the Red Cross. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, equipped well with necessary facilities for diagnosis and treatment of disabled people, has a patient assessment room, casting room, plaster modification room, sick ward, physiotherapy department room and a modern orthopedic surgical operating theater. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The center produces various kinds of prostheses, crutches and tricycles for more than 400 cripples a year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Michael Rechsteiner, head of Physical Rehabilitation Programme of the ICRC, told KCNA at the centre that the ICRC has made a contribution to treating over 2,300 disabled persons at the prosthesis center built in Songrim City, North Hwanghae Province, since it started activities in the DPRK in 2002. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
.$B!!.(BBasing itself on the already-made successes, the ICRC will impart technical skill to the employees of the newly-built center so that they can acquire a high level of technique. And in close cooperation with the Central Committee of the DPRK Red Cross Society, it will do its best so as to manufacture prostheses for disabled persons on a normal basis and make the disabled not feel any physical inconvenience, he added.
